The film combines the moods. On the one hand, we find well-documented sequences of Tehran. In the credits sequence, emblematic photographs of the time of events are shown, which were similarly portrayed in the film; there are not many differences in this regard.
On the other hand, typical Hollywood scenes are somewhat lighter, marked by irony and a slight exaggeration.
And in addition, scenes from the CIA headquarters and other institutions: costumed men analyzing the situation at the negotiating table, in the corridors of the office, by phone...
Ben Affleck has managed to restart his career in an excellent way.
