And Affleck demonstrates this in Argo, where Tehran is “wheeling” in Canada.
The best scenes of the film take place in the streets, in the reconstruction of the true events. The introductory sequence of the embassy take is impressive for its synoptic ability that, at the same time, conveys the emotion of the confusion and the lack of foresight that arises when, somewhere, the story takes a step forward.
Affleck and his collaborators achieve a similar effect in fictional scenes (the impostor team in Tehran’s bazaar).
Too much action in too many places
