In the village itself, Zodwa Dlamini, a self-assured woman with leadership skills manages the money sent from Germany.
He takes care that the orphans find a good accommodation, for example with one of the grandmothers.
The "gogos", as the older women in Zulu are called, are the pillars of the people.
