In 2001 he titled his memoirs "Hello Darlin': Tall (and Absolutely True) Tales about My Life".
“I didn’t put anything there that I thought was going to hurt someone or affect them in any way,” he told Associated Press at the time.
After the liver transplant, he became a promoter of organ donation and worked as a volunteer in a hospital to assist fearful patients.
“I advise them, I give them courage, I meet with them when they come for their surgeries, and then,” he said in 1996.
I try to offer some comfort, like "don't be afraid, it will be a little uncomfortable for a short time, but you'll be fine."
